-- Rwanda, Congo Rule Out a Joint Operation Against Rebels, New Times Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 2010-11-02T05:56:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/rwanda-congo-rule-out-another-joint-operation-on-rebels-new-times-says.html
Rwanda and the Democratic Republic of
Congo will not undertake another joint military operation
against rebel forces in eastern Congo,  New Times  reported,
citing James Kabarebe, Rwanda’s defense minister.  The size of the rebel group, Democratic Forces to Liberate
Rwanda, has been reduced by 90 percent, the Kigali-based
newspaper today cited Kabarebe as saying. Kabarebe and Congo’s
Defense Minister Charles Mwando Nsimba held talks in Kigali,
Rwanda’s capital, New Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Kigali via Johannesburg at 
1934 or  asguazzin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 